This paper deals with resource allocation optimization in a cloud radio access network (C-RAN) for multimedia applications. It involves the use of cloud computing and heterogeneous networks (HetNets), which are typically studied in the computer networks and communications (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of energy efficiency (EE) and queue stability, which are relevant topics in the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on multimedia applications, which are studied in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves mathematical optimization and analysis, which are relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
